NodeJS and AngularJS both are profitable JavaScript frameworks that are used in developing different types of web applications. NodeJS is best for building real-time and highly scalable applications. AngularJS is best for developing single-page and PAWs. Hence, depending on your use case and business objective, you should use both JS frameworks accordingly. 

After knowing the basics, architecture, types, and functioning of NodeJS and AngularJS, you might have got a clear picture of when you should use each framework to create the right web solution for your business. 

